# Cloudflare Pages headers for docs.ophis.fi (#435).
# Docusaurus copies static/_headers to the build root, which CF Pages serves.
#
# CSP scope: this site loads ONLY same-origin assets (incl. the self-hosted
# Geist woff2) and Google Tag Manager (GA4); search is the offline lunr index
# (@easyops-cn local), so connect stays same-origin. There are NO iframes,
# external images, <object>, or eval in the build (verified against the built
# output), so this enforcing policy blocks injected/external scripts, framing,
# object/embed, and base-uri hijack without breaking the site.
#
# script-src: the 'unsafe-inline' below is a FAIL-OPEN FALLBACK. The build
# postbuild step scripts/inject-csp-hashes.mjs (wired into `pnpm build`) walks
# the emitted build/**/*.html, computes the sha256 of every executable inline
# script (Docusaurus theme bootstrap, gtag consent snippet, banner bootstrap)
# and rewrites the DEPLOYED build/_headers to replace 'unsafe-inline' with that
# hash list. Browsers ignore 'unsafe-inline' once a hash is present (CSP2+), so
# if the postbuild is ever skipped the site still loads under the weaker policy
# rather than breaking. JSON-LD blocks do not execute and need no hash.
# 'wasm-unsafe-eval' is narrow (the bundle references WebAssembly) and permits
# wasm only, never JS eval ('unsafe-eval' is absent).
#
# HSTS: the Cloudflare zone-level HSTS setting is authoritative; the line below
# is a matching fallback if that setting is ever disabled.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'; frame-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://www.googletagmanager.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self'; img-src 'self' data: https:; connect-src 'self' https://www.googletagmanager.com https://*.google-analytics.com https://*.analytics.google.com; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=()
